cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CL

The paper focuses on the development of a methodology for recognizing Mediterranean food and dishes using wearable cameras, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) categories. The use of automatic mechanisms to analyze the patient's behavior and discover unhealthy food patterns suggests the involvement of machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of natural language processing (cs.CL) to extract information from recipe websites, which further supports the inclusion of this sub-category.
